                Details about what's changed
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

1) Inside GriddingAlgorithm there is some logic that invokes special handling
of the tag data when the tag buffer value is greater than the maximum ghost
width of all the data that have been registered with the PatchDescriptor.
This logic compared the value of the tag buffer to the maximum value
of the ghost width IntVector, when it really needed to compare it to every
every entry in the IntVector.  So if the tag buffer is 3 and the ghost width
is (4,4,2) the special handling should be invoked, and this bug fix makes sure
that it is.




